1)First, remove the default version supplied by the official Ubuntu repos, run commands:

sudo apt remove ansible

sudo apt --purge autoremove

2)Update Ubuntu repo and apply all pending patches:

sudo apt update

sudo apt upgrade


3)Install software-properties-common package on Ubuntu to enable PPA support, run:

sudo apt -y install software-properties-common

sudo apt-add-repository ppa:ansible/ansible

4)Finally, install the latest version of Ansible on Ubuntu Linux using the apt:

sudo apt install ansible

5)It allow you to upload Ubuntu source packages to be built and published as an apt repository by Launchpad. Type the following apt-get command or apt command:

sudo apt update

sudo apt upgrade

sudo apt install software-properties-common


6)Next add ppa:ansible/ansible to your systemâ€™s Software Source:

sudo apt-add-repository ppa:ansible/ansible

7)Next, update your repos:

sudo apt update

8)It is time to install the latest version of Ansible, enter:

sudo apt install ansible

9) Setting up Ansible bash completion support Type the following two commands:

sudo apt install python3-argcomplete

sudo activate-global-python-argcomplete3

10) Type the following command:

ansible --version

